3253 DiscreteEvent* SelfEvent::savestate_read(FILE* f) {
3254  SelfEvent* se = new SelfEvent();
3255  char buf[300];
3256  char ppname[200];
3257  int ppindex, ncindex, moff, pptype;
3258  double flag;
3259  nrn_assert(fgets(buf, 300, f));
3260  nrn_assert(
3261  sscanf(buf, "%s %d %d %d %d %lf\n", ppname, &ppindex, &pptype, &ncindex, &moff, &flag) ==
3262  6);
3263  se->target_ = SelfEvent::index2pp(pptype, ppindex);
3264  se->weight_ = nullptr;
3265  if (ncindex >= 0) {
3266  NetCon* nc = NetConSave::index2netcon(ncindex);
3267  se->weight_ = nc->weight_;
3268  }
3269  se->flag_ = flag;
3270  se->movable_ = (moff >= 0) ? (se->target_->prop->dparam + moff) : nullptr;
3271  return se;
3272 }

3276 Point_process* SelfEvent::index2pp(int type, int oindex) {
3277  // code the type and object index together
3278  if (!sepp_) {
3279  int i;
3280  sepp_.reset(new SelfEventPPTable());
3281  sepp_->reserve(211);
3282  // should only be the ones that call net_send
3283  for (i = 0; i < n_memb_func; ++i)
3284  if (pnt_receive[i]) {
3285  hoc_List* hl = nrn_pnt_template_[i]->olist;
3286  hoc_Item* q;
3287  ITERATE(q, hl) {
3288  Object* o = OBJ(q);
3289  (*sepp_)[i + n_memb_func * o->index] = ob2pntproc(o);
3290  }
3291  }
3292  }
3293  const auto& iter = sepp_->find(type + n_memb_func * oindex);
3294  nrn_assert(iter != sepp_->end());
3295  return iter->second;
3296 }

3323 void SelfEvent::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
3324  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) target_->nvi_;
3325  int type = target_->prop->_type;
3326  assert(nt == PP2NT(target_));
3327  if (nrn_use_selfqueue_ && nrn_is_artificial_[type]) { // handle possible earlier flag=1 self
3328  // event
3329  if (flag_ == 1.0) {
3330  *movable_ = nullptr;
3331  }
3332  TQItem* q;
3333  while ((q = movable_->get<TQItem*>()) != 0 && q->t_ <= tt) {
3334  // printf("handle earlier %g selfqueue event from within %g SelfEvent::deliver\n",
3335  // q->t_, tt);
3336  double t1 = q->t_;
3337  SelfEvent* se = (SelfEvent*) ns->p[nt->id].selfqueue_->remove(q);
3338  PP2t(target_) = t1;
3339  se->call_net_receive(ns);
3340  }
3341  }
3342  if (cvode_active_ && cv) {
3343  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
3344  cv->set_init_flag();
3345  } else {
3346  PP2t(target_) = tt;
3347  }
3348  // printf("SelfEvent::deliver t=%g tt=%g %s\n", PP2t(target), tt, hoc_object_name(target_->ob));
3349  call_net_receive(ns);
3350 }

3359 void SelfEvent::call_net_receive(NetCvode* ns) {
3360  STATISTICS(selfevent_deliver_);
3361  POINT_RECEIVE(target_->prop->_type, target_, weight_, flag_);
3362  if (errno) {
3363  if (nrn_errno_check(target_->prop->_type)) {
3364  hoc_warning("errno set during SelfEvent deliver to NET_RECEIVE", (char*) 0);
3365  }
3366  }
3367  NetCvodeThreadData& nctd = ns->p[PP2NT(target_)->id];
3368  --nctd.unreffed_event_cnt_;
3369  nctd.sepool_->hpfree(this);
3370 }

3453 void HocEvent::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* nc, NrnThread* nt) {
3454  extern double t;
3455  if (!ppobj_) {
3456  nc->allthread_handle(tt, this, nt);
3457  return;
3458  }
3459  if (stmt_) {
3460  if (nrn_nthread > 1 || nc->is_local()) {
3461  if (!ppobj_) {
3462  hoc_execerror(
3463  "multiple threads and/or local variable time step method require an "
3464  "appropriate POINT_PROCESS arg to CVode.event to safely execute:",
3465  stmt_->name());
3466  }
3467  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) ob2pntproc(ppobj_)->nvi_;
3468  if (cv && cvode_active_) {
3469  nc->local_retreat(tt, cv);
3470  if (reinit_) {
3471  cv->set_init_flag();
3472  }
3473  nt->_t = cv->t_;
3474  }
3475  nrn_hoc_lock();
3476  t = tt;
3477  } else if (cvode_active_ && reinit_) {
3478  nc->retreat(tt, nc->gcv_);
3479  assert(MyMath::eq(tt, nc->gcv_->t_, NetCvode::eps(tt)));
3480  assert(tt == nt->_t);
3481  nc->gcv_->set_init_flag();
3482  t = tt;
3483  } else {
3484  t = nt_t = tt;
3485  }
3486  stmt_->execute(false);
3487  if (nrn_nthread > 1 || nc->is_local()) {
3488  nrn_hoc_unlock();
3489  }
3490  }
3491  hefree();
3492 }
3493 
3494 void HocEvent::allthread_handle() {
3495  if (stmt_) {
3496  stmt_->execute(false);
3497  } else {
3498  tstopset;
3499  }
3500  hefree();
3501 }

3580 void NetCvode::local_retreat(double t, Cvode* cv) {
3581  if (!cvode_active_) {
3582  return;
3583  }
3584  TQueue* tq = p[cv->nth_ ? cv->nth_->id : 0].tq_;
3585  if (tq) {
3586 #if PRINT_EVENT
3587  if (print_event_) {
3588  Printf("microstep local retreat from %g (cvode_%p is at %g) for event onset=%g\n",
3589  cv->tqitem_->t_,
3590  cv,
3591  cv->t_,
3592  t);
3593  }
3594 #endif
3595  cv->interpolate(t);
3596  tq->move(cv->tqitem_, t);
3597 #if PRINT_EVENT
3598  if (print_event_ > 1) {
3599  Printf("after target solve time for %p is %g , dt=%g\n", cv, cv->time(), nt_dt);
3600  }
3601 #endif
3602  } else {
3603  assert(t == cv->t_ || (cv->tstop_begin_ <= t && t <= cv->tstop_end_));
3604  }
3605 }
3606 
3607 void NetCvode::retreat(double t, Cvode* cv) {
3608  if (!cvode_active_) {
3609  return;
3610  }
3611  TQueue* tq = p[cv->nth_ ? cv->nth_->id : 0].tq_;
3612 #if PRINT_EVENT
3613  if (print_event_) {
3614  Printf("microstep retreat from %g (cvode_%p is at %g) for event onset=%g\n",
3615  tq ? cv->tqitem_->t_ : cv->t_,
3616  cv,
3617  cv->t_,
3618  t);
3619  }
3620 #endif
3621  cv->interpolate(t);
3622  if (tq) {
3623  tq->move(cv->tqitem_, t);
3624  }
3625 #if PRINT_EVENT
3626  if (print_event_ > 1) {
3627  Printf("after target solve time for %p is %g , dt=%g\n", cv, cv->time(), dt);
3628  }
3629 #endif
3630 }

3634 bool neosim_deliver_self_events(TQueue* tqe, double til);
3635 bool neosim_deliver_self_events(TQueue* tqe, double til) {
3636  bool b;
3637  TQItem* q;
3638  DiscreteEvent* d;
3639  b = false;
3640  while (tqe->least_t() <= til + .5e-8) {
3641  b = true;
3642  q = tqe->least();
3643  t = q->t_;
3644  d = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
3645  assert(d->type() == SelfEventType);
3646  tqe->remove(q);
3647  d->deliver(t, net_cvode_instance);
3648  }
3649 }
3650 
3651 void neosim2nrn_advance(void* e, void* v, double tout) {
3652  neosim_entity_ = e;
3653  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
3654  TQueue* tqe;
3655 
3656  // now can integrate to tout since it is guaranteed there will
3657  // be no further real events to this cell before tout.
3658  // but we must handle self events. The implementation is
3659  // analogous to the NetCvode::solve with single and tout
3660  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) d->target_->nvi_; // so self event from INITIAL block
3661  tqe = cv->neosim_self_events_;
3662  // not a bug even if there is no BREAKPOINT block. I.e.
3663  // artificial cells will work.
3664  t = cv->time();
3665  while (tout > t) {
3666  do {
3667  cv->check_deliver();
3668  } while (neosim_deliver_self_events(tqe, t));
3669  cv->solve();
3670  }
3671  cv->interpolate(tout);
3672  cv->check_deliver();
3673 }

3677  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
3678  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) d->target_->nvi_;
3679  d->deliver(cv->t_, net_cvode_instance);
3680 }

3684 // parallel global variable time-step
3685 int NetCvode::pgvts(double tstop) {
3686  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
3687  double tt = nt_t;
3688  while (tt < tstop && !stoprun && err == NVI_SUCCESS) {
3689  err = pgvts_event(tt);
3690  }
3691  return err;
3692 }
3693 
3694 // parallel global variable time-step event handling
3695 // return is what cvode call to make and the value of tt to make it at
3696 // in response to the next global event. We try to do only one
3697 // allreduce for a given event. Since all processes have to stay together
3698 // with respect to cvode, we have to factor out those calls from the
3699 // classical DiscreteEvent::deliver methods. I.e. deliver can only
3700 // deliver an event, it cannot interpolate, etc.
3701 // Assume events are sparse and handle them one at a time.
3702 int NetCvode::pgvts_event(double& tt) {
3703  int op, err, init;
3704  DiscreteEvent* de;
3705  assert(gcv_);
3706  de = pgvts_least(tt, op, init);
3707  err = pgvts_cvode(tt, op);
3708  if (init) {
3709  gcv_->set_init_flag();
3710  }
3711  if (de) { // handle the event and others just like it
3712  de->pgvts_deliver(tt, this);
3713  while (p[0].tqe_->least_t() == tt) {
3714  TQItem* q = p[0].tqe_->least();
3715  de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
3716  int i1;
3717  if (de->pgvts_op(i1) == op && i1 == init) {
3718  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3719  de->pgvts_deliver(tt, this);
3720  } else {
3721  break;
3722  }
3723  }
3724  }
3725  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
3726  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
3727  }
3728  return err;
3729 }
3730 
3731 DiscreteEvent* NetCvode::pgvts_least(double& tt, int& op, int& init) {
3732  DiscreteEvent* de = nullptr;
3733 #if NRNMPI
3734  TQItem* q = nullptr;
3735  if (gcv_->initialize_ && p[0].tqe_->least_t() > gcv_->t_) {
3736  tt = gcv_->t_;
3737  op = 3;
3738  init = 0;
3739  } else if (gcv_->tn_ < p[0].tqe_->least_t()) {
3740  tt = gcv_->tn_;
3741  op = 1;
3742  init = 0;
3743  } else {
3744  // If there are several events at the same time we need the
3745  // highest priority (in particular, NetParEvent last).
3746  // This is due to the fact that NetParEvent.deliver
3747  // handles all the events at that time so there better not
3748  // be any after it on the queue.
3749  q = p[0].tqe_->least();
3750  if (q) {
3751  de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
3752  tt = q->t_;
3753  op = de->pgvts_op(init);
3754  if (op == 4) { // is there another event at the same time?
3755  TQItem* q2 = p[0].tqe_->second_least(tt);
3756  if (q2) {
3757  q = q2;
3758  de = (DiscreteEvent*) q2->data_;
3759  op = de->pgvts_op(init);
3760  assert(op != 4);
3761  // printf("%d Type %d event after NetParEvent with deliver %g and t=%g\n",
3762  // nrnmpi_myid, de->type(), tt, gcv_->t_);
3763  }
3764  }
3765  } else {
3766  tt = 1e20;
3767  op = 1;
3768  init = 0;
3769  }
3770  }
3771  double ts = tt;
3772  int ops = op;
3773  if (nrnmpi_pgvts_least(&tt, &op, &init)) {
3774  if (q) {
3775  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3776  }
3777  } else if (op == 4) { // NetParEvent need to be done all together
3778  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3779  } else if (ts == tt && q && ops == op) { // safe to do this event as well
3780  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3781  } else {
3782  de = nullptr;
3783  }
3784 #endif
3785  return de;
3786 }
3787 
3788 int NetCvode::pgvts_cvode(double tt, int op) {
3789  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
3790  // this is the only place where we can enter cvode
3791  switch (op) {
3792  case 1: // advance
3793  if (condition_order() == 1) {
3794  gcv_->check_deliver();
3795  }
3796  gcv_->record_continuous();
3797  err = gcv_->advance_tn(nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted());
3798  if (condition_order() == 2) {
3799  gcv_->evaluate_conditions();
3800  }
3801  break;
3802  case 2: // interpolate
3803  err = gcv_->interpolate(tt);
3804  break;
3805  case 3: // initialize
3806  err = gcv_->init(tt);
3807  initialized_ = true;
3808  if (condition_order() == 2) {
3809  gcv_->evaluate_conditions();
3810  }
3811  break;
3812  }
3813  return err;
3814 }

3818  if (gcv_) {
3819  return gcv_->use_partrans_;
3820  } else {
3821  return 0;
3822  }
3823 #endif
3824  return 0;
3825 }
3826 
3827 void ncs2nrn_integrate(double tstop) {
3828  double ts;
3829  nrn_use_busywait(1); // just a possibility
3830  auto const cache_token = nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted();
3831  if (cvode_active_) {
3832 #if NRNMPI
3833  if (net_cvode_instance->use_partrans()) {
3834  net_cvode_instance->pgvts(tstop);
3835  t = nt_t;
3836  dt = nt_dt;
3837  } else
3838 #endif
3839  {
3840  net_cvode_instance->solve(tstop);
3841  t = nt_t;
3842  dt = nt_dt;
3843  }
3844  } else {
3845 #if 1
3846  int n = (int) ((tstop - nt_t) / dt + 1e-9);
3847  if (n > 3 && !nrnthread_v_transfer_) {
3848  nrn_fixed_step_group(cache_token, n);
3849  } else
3850 #endif
3851  {
3852 #if NRNMPI && !defined(USENCS)
3853  ts = tstop - dt;
3854  assert(nt_t <= tstop);
3855  // It may very well be the case that we do not advance at all
3856  while (nt_t <= ts) {
3857 #else
3858  ts = tstop - .5 * dt;
3859  while (nt_t < ts) {
3860 #endif
3861  nrn_fixed_step(cache_token);
3862  if (stoprun) {
3863  break;
3864  }
3865  }
3866  }
3867  }
3868  // handle all the pending flag=1 self events
3869  for (int i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
3870  assert(nrn_threads[i]._t == nt_t);
3871  }
3872  all_pending_selfqueue(nt_t);
3873  nrn_use_busywait(0); // certainly not
3874 }
3875 
3876 TQueue* NetCvode::event_queue(NrnThread* nt) {
3877  return p[nt->id].tqe_;
3878 }
3879 
3880 static double pending_selfqueue_deliver_;
3881 static void* pending_selfqueue(NrnThread* nt) {
3882  nrn_pending_selfqueue(pending_selfqueue_deliver_, nt);
3883  return 0;
3884 }
3885 
3886 void nrn_pending_selfqueue(double tt, NrnThread* nt) {
3887  NetCvodeThreadData& nctd = net_cvode_instance->p[nt->id];
3888  double ts = nt->_t;
3889  // net_cvode_instance->deliver_events(nctd.immediate_deliver_, nt);
3890  SelfQueue* sq = nctd.selfqueue_;
3891  TQItem *q1, *q2;
3892  nctd.immediate_deliver_ = tt;
3893  for (q1 = sq->first(); q1; q1 = q2) {
3894  if (q1->t_ <= tt) {
3895  SelfEvent* se = (SelfEvent*) q1->data_;
3896  // printf("ncs2nrn_integrate %g SelfEvent for %s at %g\n", tstop,
3897  // hoc_object_name(se->target_->ob), q1->t_);
3898  se->deliver(q1->t_, net_cvode_instance, nt);
3899  // could it add another self-event?, check before removal
3900  q2 = sq->next(q1);
3901  sq->remove(q1);
3902  } else {
3903  q2 = sq->next(q1);
3904  }
3905  }
3906  assert(nctd.tqe_->least_t() >= tt);
3907  nt->_t = ts;
3908  nctd.immediate_deliver_ = -1e100;
3909 }
3910 
3911 // only the main thread can calls this
3912 static void all_pending_selfqueue(double tt) {
3913  if (nrn_use_selfqueue_) {
3914  nrn_wait_for_threads();
3915  // for (int i=0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) { assert(nrn_threads[i]._t == nt_t);}
3916  pending_selfqueue_deliver_ = tt;
3917  nrn_multithread_job(pending_selfqueue);
3918  }
3919 }

4027 void NetCvode::spike_stat() {
4028  Vect* v = vector_arg(1);
4029  v->resize(11);
4030  double* d = vector_vec(v);
4031  int i, j, n = 0;
4032  if (gcv_) {
4033  n += gcv_->neq_;
4034  } else {
4035  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4036  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4037  }
4038  }
4039  d[0] = n;
4040  Symbol* nc = hoc_lookup("NetCon");
4041  d[1] = nc->u.ctemplate->count;
4042  d[2] = deliver_cnt_;
4043  d[3] = NetCon::netcon_deliver_;
4044  d[4] = PreSyn::presyn_send_mindelay_ + PreSyn::presyn_send_direct_;
4045  d[5] = SelfEvent::selfevent_deliver_;
4046  d[6] = SelfEvent::selfevent_send_;
4047  d[7] = SelfEvent::selfevent_move_;
4048  // should do all threads
4049  p[0].tqe_->spike_stat(d + 8);
4050 }
4051 
4052 void NetCvode::solver_prepare() {
4053  int i, j;
4054  fornetcon_prepare();
4055  if (nrn_modeltype() == 0) {
4056  delete_list();
4057  } else {
4058  init_global();
4059  if (cvode_active_) {
4060  if (matrix_change_cnt_ != nrn_matrix_cnt_) {
4061  structure_change();
4062  matrix_change_cnt_ = nrn_matrix_cnt_;
4063  }
4064  if (gcv_) {
4065  gcv_->use_daspk_ = nrn_use_daspk_;
4066  gcv_->init_prepare();
4067  // since there may be Vector.play events and INITIAL send events
4068  // at time 0 before actual initialization of integrators.
4069  gcv_->can_retreat_ = false;
4070  } else {
4071  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4072  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
4073  cv.use_daspk_ = nrn_use_daspk_;
4074  cv.init_prepare();
4075  cv.can_retreat_ = false;
4076  }
4077  }
4078  }
4079  }
4080  if (playrec_change_cnt_ != structure_change_cnt_) {
4081  playrec_setup();
4082  }
4083 }
4084 
4085 void NetCvode::re_init(double t) {
4086  int i, j;
4087  if (nrn_modeltype() == 0) {
4088  if (gcv_) {
4089  gcv_->t_ = t;
4090  gcv_->tn_ = t;
4091  } else {
4092  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4093  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
4094  cv.t_ = t;
4095  cv.tn_ = t;
4096  }
4097  }
4098  return;
4099  }
4100  double dtsav = nt_dt;
4101  solver_prepare();
4102  if (gcv_) {
4103  gcv_->stat_init();
4104  gcv_->init(t);
4105  if (condition_order() == 2) {
4106  gcv_->evaluate_conditions();
4107  }
4108  } else {
4109  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4110  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
4111  cv.stat_init();
4112  cv.init(t);
4113  cv.tqitem_->t_ = t;
4114  if (condition_order() == 2) {
4115  cv.evaluate_conditions();
4116  }
4117  }
4118  }
4119  nt_dt = dtsav;
4120 }
4121 
4122 void NetCvode::fornetcon_prepare() {
4123  NrnThread* nt;
4124  NrnThreadMembList* tml;
4125  if (fornetcon_change_cnt_ == structure_change_cnt) {
4126  return;
4127  }
4128  fornetcon_change_cnt_ = structure_change_cnt;
4129  if (nrn_fornetcon_cnt_ == 0) {
4130  return;
4131  }
4132  int i, j;
4133  // initialize a map from type to dparam index, -1 means no FOR_NETCONS statement
4134  std::vector<int> t2i(n_memb_func, -1);
4135  // create ForNetConsInfo in all the relevant point processes
4136  // and fill in the t2i map.
4137  for (i = 0; i < nrn_fornetcon_cnt_; ++i) {
4138  int index = nrn_fornetcon_index_[i];
4139  int type = nrn_fornetcon_type_[i];
4140  t2i[type] = index;
4141  if (nrn_is_artificial_[type]) {
4142  auto* const m = &memb_list[type];
4143  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
4144  // Save ForNetConsInfo* as void* to avoid needing to expose the
4145  // definition of ForNetConsInfo to translated MOD file code
4146  void** v = &(m->pdata[j][index].literal_value<void*>());
4147  _nrn_free_fornetcon(v);
4148  ForNetConsInfo* fnc = new ForNetConsInfo;
4149  *v = fnc;
4150  fnc->argslist = 0;
4151  fnc->size = 0;
4152  }
4153  } else {
4154  FOR_THREADS(nt) for (tml = nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next) if (tml->index == type) {
4155  Memb_list* m = tml->ml;
4156  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
4157  void** v = &(m->pdata[j][index].literal_value<void*>());
4158  _nrn_free_fornetcon(v);
4159  ForNetConsInfo* fnc = new ForNetConsInfo;
4160  *v = fnc;
4161  fnc->argslist = 0;
4162  fnc->size = 0;
4163  }
4164  }
4165  }
4166  }
4167  // two loops over all netcons. one to count, one to fill in argslist
4168  // count
4169  hoc_Item* q;
4170  if (psl_)
4171  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
4172  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
4173  const NetConPList& dil = ps->dil_;
4174  for (const auto& d1: dil) {
4175  Point_process* pnt = d1->target_;
4176  if (pnt && t2i[pnt->prop->_type] > -1) {
4177  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(
4178  pnt->prop->dparam[t2i[pnt->prop->_type]].get<void*>());
4179  assert(fnc);
4180  fnc->size += 1;
4181  }
4182  }
4183  }
4184 
4185  // allocate argslist space and initialize for another count
4186  for (i = 0; i < nrn_fornetcon_cnt_; ++i) {
4187  int index = nrn_fornetcon_index_[i];
4188  int type = nrn_fornetcon_type_[i];
4189  if (nrn_is_artificial_[type]) {
4190  auto* const m = &memb_list[type];
4191  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
4192  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(m->pdata[j][index].get<void*>());
4193  if (fnc->size > 0) {
4194  fnc->argslist = new double*[fnc->size];
4195  fnc->size = 0;
4196  }
4197  }
4198  } else {
4199  FOR_THREADS(nt)
4200  for (tml = nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next)
4201  if (tml->index == nrn_fornetcon_type_[i]) {
4202  Memb_list* m = tml->ml;
4203  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
4204  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(m->pdata[j][index].get<void*>());
4205  if (fnc->size > 0) {
4206  fnc->argslist = new double*[fnc->size];
4207  fnc->size = 0;
4208  }
4209  }
4210  }
4211  }
4212  }
4213  // fill in argslist and count again
4214  if (psl_) {
4215  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
4216  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
4217  const NetConPList& dil = ps->dil_;
4218  for (const auto& d1: dil) {
4219  Point_process* pnt = d1->target_;
4220  if (pnt && t2i[pnt->prop->_type] > -1) {
4221  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(
4222  pnt->prop->dparam[t2i[pnt->prop->_type]].get<void*>());
4223  fnc->argslist[fnc->size] = d1->weight_;
4224  fnc->size += 1;
4225  }
4226  }
4227  }
4228  }
4229 }
4230 
4231 int _nrn_netcon_args(void* v, double*** argslist) {
4232  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(v);
4233  assert(fnc);
4234  *argslist = fnc->argslist;
4235  return fnc->size;
4236 }

4238 void _nrn_free_fornetcon(void** v) {

4240  delete[] std::exchange(fnc->argslist, nullptr);
4241  delete fnc;
4242  *v = nullptr;
4243  }
4244 }

4273 int NetCvode::cellindex() {

4299  n += gcv_->neq_;

4303  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;

4313  p[i].lcv_[j].states(vp + k);
4314  k += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4315  }
4316  }

4358 double nrn_hoc2fun(void* v) {

4465 /** @brief Create a lookup table for variable names.
4466  *
4467  * This is only created on-demand because it involves building a lookup table
4468  * of pointers, some of which are obtained from data_handles (and are therefore
4469  * unstable). Eventually the operator<< of data_handle might provide the
4470  * necessary functionality and this could be dropped completely.
4471  */
4472 HocDataPaths NetCvode::create_hdp(int style) {
4473  int n{};
4474  if (gcv_) {
4475  n += gcv_->neq_;
4476  } else {
4477  int i, j;
4478  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4479  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4480  }
4481  }
4482  HocDataPaths hdp{2 * n, style};
4483  if (gcv_) {
4484  for (int it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
4485  CvodeThreadData& z = gcv_->ctd_[it];
4486  for (int j = 0; j < z.nonvint_extra_offset_; ++j) {
4487  hdp.append(static_cast<double*>(z.pv_[j]));
4488  }
4489  }
4490  } else {
4491  int i, it;
4492  lvardtloop(it, i) {
4493  auto const neq = p[it].lcv_[i].ctd_[0].nvsize_;
4494  auto& pv = p[it].lcv_[i].ctd_[0].pv_;
4495  for (int j = 0; j < neq; ++j) {
4496  hdp.append(static_cast<double*>(pv[j]));
4497  }
4498  }
4499  }
4500  hdp.search();
4501  return hdp;
4502 }
4503 
4504 std::string NetCvode::statename(int is, int style) {
4505  if (!cvode_active_) {
4506  hoc_execerror("Cvode is not active", 0);
4507  }
4508  auto const n = [&]() {
4509  int n{};
4510  if (gcv_) {
4511  n += gcv_->neq_;
4512  } else {
4513  int i, j;
4514  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4515  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4516  }
4517  }
4518  return n;
4519  }();
4520  if (is >= n) {
4521  hoc_execerror("Cvode::statename argument out of range", nullptr);
4522  }
4523  auto const impl = [hdp = create_hdp(style), style, this](auto& handle) -> std::string {
4524  auto* const raw_ptr = static_cast<double*>(handle);
4525  if (style == 2) {
4526  auto* sym = hdp.retrieve_sym(raw_ptr);
4527  assert(sym);
4528  return sym2name(sym);
4529  } else {
4530  std::string s = hdp.retrieve(raw_ptr);
4531  return !s.empty() ? s.c_str() : "unknown";
4532  }
4533  };
4534  int j{};
4535  if (gcv_) {
4536  for (int it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
4537  CvodeThreadData& z = gcv_->ctd_[it];
4538  if (j + z.nvoffset_ + z.nvsize_ > is) {
4539  return impl(z.pv_[is - j]);
4540  }
4541  j += z.nvsize_;
4542  }
4543  } else {
4544  int it, i;
4545  lvardtloop(it, i) {
4546  if (j + p[it].lcv_[i].neq_ > is) {
4547  CvodeThreadData& z = p[it].lcv_[i].ctd_[0];
4548  return impl(z.pv_[is - j]);
4549  }
4550  j += p[it].lcv_[i].neq_;
4551  }
4552  }
4553  return "unknown";
4554 }

4556 const char* NetCvode::sym2name(Symbol* sym) {
4557  if (sym->type == RANGEVAR && sym->u.rng.type > 1 && memb_func[sym->u.rng.type].is_point) {
4558  static char buf[200];
4559  Sprintf(buf, "%s.%s", memb_func[sym->u.rng.type].sym->name, sym->name);
4560  return buf;
4561  } else {
4562  return sym->name;
4563  }
4564 }
4565 
4566 Symbol* NetCvode::name2sym(const char* name) {
4567  std::vector<char> buf(strlen(name) + 1);
4568  strcpy(buf.data(), name);
4569  char* cp;
4570  for (cp = buf.data(); *cp; ++cp) {
4571  if (*cp == '.') {
4572  *cp = '\0';
4573  ++cp;
4574  break;
4575  }
4576  }
4577  Symbol* sym = hoc_table_lookup(buf.data(), hoc_built_in_symlist);
4578  if (!sym) {
4579  sym = hoc_table_lookup(buf.data(), hoc_top_level_symlist);
4580  }
4581  if (sym && *cp == '\0' && (sym->type == RANGEVAR || strcmp(sym->name, "Vector") == 0)) {
4582  return sym;
4583  } else if (sym && sym->type == TEMPLATE && *cp != '\0') {
4584  sym = hoc_table_lookup(cp, sym->u.ctemplate->symtable);
4585  if (sym) {
4586  return sym;
4587  }
4588  }
4589  hoc_execerror(name, "must be in form rangevar or Template.var");
4590  return nullptr;
4591 }

4675 NetCon* NetCvode::install_deliver(neuron::container::data_handle<double> dsrc,
4676  Section* ssrc,
4677  Object* osrc,
4678  Object* target,
4679  double threshold,
4680  double delay,
4681  double magnitude) {
4682  PreSyn* ps = nullptr;
4683  neuron::container::data_handle<double> psrc{};
4684  if (ssrc) {
4685  consist_sec_pd("NetCon", ssrc, dsrc);
4686  }
4687  if (!pst_) {
4688  pst_ = new PreSynTable(1000);
4689  pst_cnt_ = 0;
4690  }
4691  if (!psl_) {
4692  psl_ = hoc_l_newlist();
4693  }
4694  if (osrc) {
4695  assert(!dsrc);
4696  char buf[256];
4697  if (hoc_table_lookup("x", osrc->ctemplate->symtable)) {
4698  Point_process* pp = ob2pntproc(osrc);
4699  assert(pp && pp->prop);
4700  if (!pnt_receive[pp->prop->_type]) { // only if no NET_RECEIVE block
4701  Sprintf(buf, "%s.x", hoc_object_name(osrc));
4702  psrc = hoc_val_handle(buf);
4703  }
4704  }
4705  } else {
4706  psrc = dsrc;
4707  }
4708  if (psrc) {
4709  auto psti = pst_->find(psrc);
4710  if (psti == pst_->end()) {
4711  ps = new PreSyn(psrc, osrc, ssrc);
4712  ps->hi_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(psl_, ps);
4713  (*pst_)[psrc] = ps;
4714  ++pst_cnt_;
4715  } else {
4716  ps = psti->second;
4717  }
4718  if (threshold != -1e9) {
4719  ps->threshold_ = threshold;
4720  }
4721  } else if (osrc) {
4722  Point_process* pnt = ob2pntproc(osrc);
4723  if (pnt->presyn_) {
4724  ps = (PreSyn*) pnt->presyn_;
4725  } else {
4726  ps = new PreSyn(psrc, osrc, ssrc);
4727  if (threshold != -1e9) {
4728  ps->threshold_ = threshold;
4729  }
4730  ps->hi_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(psl_, ps);
4731  pnt->presyn_ = ps;
4732  }
4733  } else if (target) { // no source so use the special presyn
4734  if (!unused_presyn) {
4735  unused_presyn = new PreSyn({}, nullptr, nullptr);
4736  unused_presyn->hi_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(psl_, unused_presyn);
4737  }
4738  ps = unused_presyn;
4739  }
4740  ps_thread_link(ps);
4741  NetCon* d = new NetCon(ps, target);
4742  d->delay_ = delay;
4743  d->weight_[0] = magnitude;
4744  structure_change_cnt_ = 0;
4745  return d;
4746 }
4747 
4748 void NetCvode::psl_append(PreSyn* ps) {
4749  if (!psl_) {
4750  psl_ = hoc_l_newlist();
4751  }
4752  ps->hi_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(psl_, ps);
4753 }

4755 void NetCvode::presyn_disconnect(PreSyn* ps) {
4756  if (ps == unused_presyn) {
4757  unused_presyn = nullptr;
4758  }
4759  if (ps->hi_) {
4760  hoc_l_delete(ps->hi_);
4761  ps->hi_ = nullptr;
4762  }
4763  if (ps->hi_th_) {
4764  hoc_l_delete(ps->hi_th_);
4765  ps->hi_th_ = nullptr;
4766  }
4767  if (ps->thvar_) {
4768  --pst_cnt_;
4769  pst_->erase(ps->thvar_);
4770  ps->thvar_ = {};
4771  }
4772  if (gcv_) {
4773  for (int it = 0; it < gcv_->nctd_; ++it) {
4774  PreSynList* psl = gcv_->ctd_[it].psl_th_;
4775  if (psl)
4776  for (size_t j = 0; j < psl->size(); ++j) {
4777  if ((*psl)[j] == ps) {
4778  psl->erase(psl->begin() + j);
4779  return;
4780  }
4781  }
4782  }
4783  } else {
4784  int i, j;
4785  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4786  PreSynList* psl = p[i].lcv_[j].ctd_[0].psl_th_;
4787  if (psl)
4788  for (size_t j = 0; j < psl->size(); ++j) {
4789  if ((*psl)[j] == ps) {
4790  psl->erase(psl->begin() + j);
4791  return;
4792  }
4793  }
4794  }
4795  }
4796 }

4873 void NetCon::rmsrc() {
4874  if (src_) {
4875  for (size_t i = 0; i < src_->dil_.size(); ++i) {
4876  if (src_->dil_[i] == this) {
4877  src_->dil_.erase(src_->dil_.begin() + i);
4878  if (src_->dil_.size() == 0 && src_->tvec_ == NULL && src_->idvec_ == NULL) {
4879  if (src_->output_index_ == -1) {
4880  delete std::exchange(src_, nullptr);
4881  }
4882  }
4883  break;
4884  }
4885  }
4886  }
4887  src_ = nullptr;
4888 }

4945 NetCon* NetConSave::weight2netcon(double* pd) {
4946  NetCon* nc;
4947  if (!wtable_) {
4948  hoc_Item* q;
4949  Symbol* sym = hoc_lookup("NetCon");
4950  wtable_ = new NetConSaveWeightTable(2 * sym->u.ctemplate->count);
4951  ITERATE(q, sym->u.ctemplate->olist) {
4952  Object* obj = OBJ(q);
4953  nc = (NetCon*) obj->u.this_pointer;
4954  if (nc->weight_) {
4955  (*wtable_)[nc->weight_] = nc;
4956  }
4957  }
4958  }
4959  auto wti = wtable_->find(pd);
4960  if (wti != wtable_->end()) {
4961  nc = wti->second;
4962  assert(nc->weight_ == pd);
4963  return nc;
4964  } else {
4965  return nullptr;
4966  }
4967 }

4997 void NetCvode::ps_thread_link(PreSyn* ps) {
4998  if (!ps) {
4999  return;
5000  }
5001  ps->nt_ = nullptr;
5002  if (!v_structure_change) { // PP2NT etc are correct
5003  if (ps->osrc_) {
5004  ps->nt_ = PP2NT(ob2pntproc(ps->osrc_));
5005  } else if (ps->ssrc_) {
5006  ps->nt_ = ps->ssrc_->prop->dparam[9].get<NrnThread*>();
5007  }
5008  }
5009  if (!ps->nt_) { // premature, reorder_secorder() not called yet
5010  return;
5011  }
5012  if (ps->thvar_) {
5013  int i = ps->nt_->id;
5014  if (!p[i].psl_thr_) {
5015  p[i].psl_thr_ = hoc_l_newlist();
5016  }
5017  ps->hi_th_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(p[i].psl_thr_, ps);
5018  }
5019 }

5021 void NetCvode::update_ps2nt() {
5022  int i;
5023  // first, opportunistically create p[]
5024  p_construct(nrn_nthread);
5025  // iterate over all threshold PreSyn and fill the NrnThread field
5026  hoc_Item* q;
5027  for (i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
5028  if (p[i].psl_thr_) {
5029  hoc_l_freelist(&p[i].psl_thr_);
5030  }
5031  }
5032  if (psl_)
5033  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
5034  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
5035  ps_thread_link(ps);
5036  }
5037 }

5044  p = new NetCvodeThreadData[n];
5045  }
5046  pcnt_ = n;
5047  }
5048  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
5049  p[i].unreffed_event_cnt_ = 0;
5050  }
5051 }

5175  ++cnt;

5184  ++cnt;
5185  }

5244 void PreSyn::record(double tt) {
5245  if (tvec_) {
5246  // need to lock the vector if shared by other PreSyn
5247  // since we get here in the thread that manages the
5248  // threshold detection (or net_event from NET_RECEIVE).
5249  if (idvec_) {
5250  tvec_->lock();
5251  }
5252  tvec_->push_back(tt);
5253  if (idvec_) {
5254  idvec_->push_back(rec_id_);
5255  tvec_->unlock();
5256  }
5257  }
5258  if (stmt_) {
5259  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
5260  nrn_hoc_lock();
5261  }
5262  t = tt;
5263  stmt_->execute(false);
5264  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
5265  nrn_hoc_unlock();
5266  }
5267  }
5268 }

5270 void PreSyn::disconnect(Observable* o) {
5271  // printf("PreSyn::disconnect %s\n", hoc_object_name(((ObjObservable*)o)->object()));
5272  if (tvec_ && tvec_->obj_ == ((ObjObservable*) o)->object()) {
5273  tvec_ = nullptr;
5274  }
5275  if (idvec_ && idvec_->obj_ == ((ObjObservable*) o)->object()) {
5276  idvec_ = nullptr;
5277  }
5278  if (dil_.size() == 0 && tvec_ == nullptr && idvec_ == nullptr && output_index_ == -1) {
5279  delete this;
5280  }
5281 }

5283 void PreSyn::update(Observable* o) { // should be disconnect
5284  // printf("PreSyn::update\n");
5285  for (const auto& d: dil_) {
5286 #if 0 // osrc_ below is invalid
5287 if (d->obj_) {
5288  printf("%s disconnect from ", hoc_object_name(d->obj_));
5289  printf("source %s\n", osrc_ ? hoc_object_name(osrc_) : secname(ssrc_));
5290 }
5291 #endif
5292  d->src_ = nullptr;
5293  }
5294  if (tvec_) {
5295 #if DISCRETE_EVENT_OBSERVER
5296  ObjObservable::Detach(tvec_->obj_, this);
5297 #endif
5298  tvec_ = nullptr;
5299  }
5300  if (idvec_) {
5301 #if DISCRETE_EVENT_OBSERVER
5302  ObjObservable::Detach(idvec_->obj_, this);
5303 #endif
5304  idvec_ = nullptr;

5306  net_cvode_instance->presyn_disconnect(this);
5307  thvar_ = {};
5308  osrc_ = nullptr;

5312 void ConditionEvent::check(NrnThread* nt, double tt, double teps) {
5313  if (value() > 0.0) {
5314  if (flag_ == false) {
5315  flag_ = true;
5316  valthresh_ = 0.;
5317 #if USENEOSIM
5318  if (neosim_entity_) {
5319  (*p_nrn2neosim_send)(neosim_entity_, tt);
5320  } else {
5321 #endif
5322  send(tt + teps, net_cvode_instance, nt);
5323 #if USENEOSIM
5324  }
5325 #endif
5326  }
5327  } else {
5328  flag_ = false;
5329  }
5330 }

5338 void ConditionEvent::condition(Cvode* cv) { // logic for high order threshold detection
5339  // printf("ConditionEvent::condition f=%d t=%20.15g v=%20.15g\n", flag_, t, value());
5340  NrnThread* nt = thread();
5341  if (qthresh_) { // the threshold event has not
5342  // been handled. i.e. the cell must have retreated to
5343  // a time not later than the threshold time.
5344  assert(nt->_t <= qthresh_->t_);
5345  abandon_statistics(cv);
5346  // abandon the event
5347  STATISTICS(abandon_);
5348  net_cvode_instance->remove_event(qthresh_, nt->id);
5349  qthresh_ = nullptr;
5350  valthresh_ = 0.;
5351  flag_ = false;
5352  }
5353 
5354  double val = value();
5355  if (flag_ == false && val >= 0.0) { // above threshold
5356  flag_ = true;
5357  valthresh_ = 0.;
5358  if (cv->t0_ == cv->tn_) { // inited
5359  // means immediate threshold event now.
5360  // no need for qthresh since there is
5361  // no question of abandoning it so instead
5362  // of a qthresh it is a send event.
5363  STATISTICS(init_above_);
5364  send(nt->_t, net_cvode_instance, nt);
5365  } else { // crossed somewhere in the told to t interval
5366  STATISTICS(send_qthresh_);
5367  // reset the flag_ when the value goes lower than
5368  // valold since value() when qthresh_ handled
5369  // may in fact be below 0.0
5370  valthresh_ = valold_;
5371  double th = -valold_ / (val - valold_);
5372  th = th * nt->_t + (1. - th) * told_;
5373  assert(th >= cv->t0_ && th <= cv->tn_);
5374  qthresh_ = net_cvode_instance->event(th, this, nt);
5375  }
5376  } else if (flag_ == true && valold_ < valthresh_ && val < valthresh_) {
5377  // below threshold
5378  // previous step crossed in negative direction
5379  // and there was not any retreat or initialization
5380  // to give spurious crossing.
5381  flag_ = false;
5382  }
5383  valold_ = val;
5384  told_ = nt->_t;
5385 }
5386 
5387 double STECondition::value() {
5388  double val = stet_->value();
5389  return val;
5390 }
5391 
5392 void ConditionEvent::abandon_statistics(Cvode* cv) {
5393 #if 1
5394  // printf("ConditionEvent::condition %s t=%20.15g abandon event at %20.15g\n",
5395  // ssrc_?secname(ssrc_):"", t, qthresh_->t_);
5396  if (nt_t == qthresh_->t_) { // it is not clear whether
5397  // this could happen and if it does it may
5398  // take fastidiousness to
5399  // an extreme
5400  STATISTICS(eq_abandon_);
5401  Printf("abandon when t == qthresh_->t_ = %20.15g\n", nt_t);
5402  }
5403  if (cv->t0_ == cv->tn_) { // inited
5404  if (value() > 0.0) { // above threshold
5405  STATISTICS(abandon_init_above_);
5406  } else {
5407  STATISTICS(abandon_init_below_);
5408  }
5409  } else {
5410  if (value() > 0.0) { // above threshold
5411  STATISTICS(abandon_above_);
5412  } else {
5413  STATISTICS(abandon_below_);
5414  }
5415  }
5416 #endif
5417 }

5441 void WatchCondition::activate(double flag) {
5442  Cvode* cv = NULL;
5443  int id = 0;
5444  qthresh_ = nullptr;
5445  flag_ = (value() >= -hoc_epsilon) ? true : false;
5446  valthresh_ = 0.;
5447  nrflag_ = flag;
5448  if (!pnt_) { // possible for StateTransitionEvent
5449  // but only if 1 thread and no lvardt
5450  assert(nrn_nthread == 1);
5451  assert(net_cvode_instance->localstep() == false);
5452  cv = net_cvode_instance->gcv_;
5453  } else {
5454  cv = (Cvode*) pnt_->nvi_;
5455  }
5456  assert(cv);
5457  id = (cv->nctd_ > 1) ? thread()->id : 0;
5458  HTList*& wl = cv->ctd_[id].watch_list_;
5459  if (!wl) {
5460  wl = new HTList(nullptr);
5461  net_cvode_instance->wl_list_[id].push_back(wl);
5462  }
5463  Remove();
5464  wl->Append(this);
5465 }

5480 void WatchCondition::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
5481  if (qthresh_) {
5482  qthresh_ = nullptr;
5483  STATISTICS(deliver_qthresh_);
5484  }
5485  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) pnt_->nvi_;
5486  int type = pnt_->prop->_type;
5487  if (cvode_active_ && cv) {
5488  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
5489  cv->set_init_flag();
5490  } else {
5491  PP2t(pnt_) = tt;
5492  }
5493  STATISTICS(watch_deliver_);
5494  POINT_RECEIVE(type, pnt_, nullptr, nrflag_);
5495  if (errno) {
5496  if (nrn_errno_check(type)) {
5497  hoc_warning("errno set during WatchCondition deliver to NET_RECEIVE", (char*) 0);
5498  }
5499  }
5500 }

5536 void STECondition::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {

5546  cv->set_init_flag();

5553  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
5554  cv->set_init_flag();
5555  } else {
5556  PP2t(pnt_) = tt;
5557  }
5558  }
5559  STATISTICS(watch_deliver_);
5560  t = tt;
5561  stet_->event();
5562 }

5614 static Cvode* eval_cv;
5615 static void* eval_cond(NrnThread* nt) {
5616  eval_cv->evaluate_conditions(nt);
5617  return 0;
5618 }
5619 void Cvode::evaluate_conditions(NrnThread* nt) {
5620  if (!nt) {
5621  if (nrn_nthread > 1 && nctd_ > 1) {
5622  eval_cv = this;
5623  nrn_multithread_job(eval_cond);
5624  return;
5625  }
5626  nt = nrn_threads;
5627  }
5628  CvodeThreadData& z = CTD(nt->id);
5629  if (z.psl_th_) {
5630  // originally was a reverse iteration, but I thing that was
5631  // just to avoid continually calling count() on the List.
5632  for (auto ps: *(z.psl_th_)) {
5633  ps->condition(this);
5634  }
5635  }
5636  if (z.watch_list_) {
5637  for (HTList* item = z.watch_list_->First(); item != z.watch_list_->End();
5638  item = item->Next()) {
5639  ((WatchCondition*) item)->condition(this);
5640  }
5641  }
5642 }
5643 
5644 static void* chk_deliv(NrnThread* nt) {
5645  eval_cv->check_deliver(nt);
5646  return 0;
5647 }
5648 void Cvode::check_deliver(NrnThread* nt) {
5649  if (!nt) {
5650  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
5651  eval_cv = this;
5652  nrn_multithread_job(chk_deliv);
5653  return;
5654  }
5655  nt = nrn_threads;
5656  }
5657  CvodeThreadData& z = CTD(nt->id);
5658  if (z.psl_th_) {
5659  // originally was a reverse iteration, but I thing that was
5660  // just to avoid continually calling count() on the List.
5661  for (auto ps: *(z.psl_th_)) {
5662  ps->check(nt, nt->_t);
5663  }
5664  }
5665  if (z.watch_list_) {
5666  for (HTList* item = z.watch_list_->First(); item != z.watch_list_->End();
5667  item = item->Next()) {
5668  ((WatchCondition*) item)->check(nt, nt->_t);
5669  }
5670  }
5671 }

5691 // nrnthread_get_trajectory_requests helper for buffered trajectories
5692 // also for per time step return (no Vector and varrays is NULL)
5693 // if bsize > 0 then CoreNEURON will write that number of values to the vectors.
5694 // If CoreNEURON has a start time > 0, (current value of t),
5695 // the amount to augment the vector depends
5696 // on the vector's current size in the current NEURON context and the
5697 // varray[i_trajec] double* will be determined by that current size.
5698 // However determination of whether to do per time step return or buffering
5699 // can be specified on the NEURON side.
5700 static int trajec_buffered(NrnThread& nt,
5701  int bsize,
5702  IvocVect* v,
5703  neuron::container::data_handle<double> pd,
5704  int i_pr,
5705  PlayRecord* pr,
5706  void** vpr,
5707  int i_trajec,
5708  int* types,
5709  int* indices,
5710  double** pvars,
5711  double** varrays) {
5712  int err = 0; // success
5713  if (bsize > 0) {
5714  int cur_size = v->size();
5715  if (v->buffer_size() < bsize + cur_size) {
5716  v->buffer_size(bsize + cur_size);
5717  }
5718  // nrnthread_trajectory_values will resize to correct size.
5719  v->resize(bsize + cur_size);
5720  varrays[i_trajec] = vector_vec(v) + cur_size; // begin filling here
5721  } else {
5722  // Danger, think this through better
5723  pvars[i_trajec] = static_cast<double*>(pd);
5724  }
5725  vpr[i_pr] = pr;
5726  if (static_cast<double const*>(pd) == &nt._t) {
5727  types[i_trajec] = 0;
5728  indices[i_trajec] = 0;
5729  } else {
5730  err = nrn_dblpntr2nrncore(pd, nt, types[i_trajec], indices[i_trajec]);
5731  if (err) {
5732  Fprintf(stderr,
5733  "Pointer %p of PlayRecord type %d ignored because not a Range Variable",
5734  static_cast<double*>(pd),
5735  pr->type());
5736  }
5737  }
5738  return err;
5739 }
5740 
5741 // Transfer of trajectories from CoreNEURON to NEURON.
5742 // bsize == 0: Most flexible interactivity, transfer on a per time step basis.
5743 // bsize > 0: Greatest performance, fill the entire trajectory arrays on
5744 // the CoreNEURON side and transferring at the end of a CoreNEURON run.
5745 // Here, we ensure the arrays have at least bsize size (i.e. at least tstop/dt)
5746 // beyond their current size and CoreNEURON will start filling from the
5747 // current fill time, h.t, location of the arrays. I.e. starting at CoreNEURON's
5748 // start time. (Multiple calls to psolve append to these arrays.)
5749 // n_pr refers to the number of PlayRecord instances in the vpr array.
5750 // n_trajec refers to the number of trajectories to be recorded on the
5751 // CoreNEURON side and is the size of the types, indices, and varrays.
5752 // n_pr is different from n_trajec when one of the GLineRecord instances has
5753 // a gl_->name that is an expression that contains several range variables.
5754 // Per time step transfer now uses pvars so CoreNEURON scatters values
5755 // to pvars instead of collecting in double array.
5756 void nrnthread_get_trajectory_requests(int tid,
5757  int& bsize,
5758  int& n_pr,
5759  void**& vpr,
5760  int& n_trajec,
5761  int*& types,
5762  int*& indices,
5763  double**& pvars,
5764  double**& varrays) {
5765  if (bsize > 0) { // but would NEURON rather use per time step mode
5766  if (nrn_trajectory_request_per_time_step_) {
5767  bsize = 0;
5768  }
5769  }
5770  n_pr = 0;
5771  n_trajec = 0;
5772  types = NULL;
5773  indices = NULL;
5774  vpr = NULL;
5775  varrays = NULL;
5776  pvars = NULL;
5777  if (tid < nrn_nthread) {
5778  NrnThread& nt = nrn_threads[tid];
5779  auto* fr = net_cvode_instance->fixed_record_;
5780  // allocate
5781  for (auto& pr: *fr) {
5782  if (pr->ith_ == tid) {
5783  if (pr->type() == TvecRecordType || pr->type() == YvecRecordType) {
5784  n_pr++;
5785  n_trajec++;
5786 #if HAVE_IV
5787  } else if (pr->type() == GLineRecordType) {
5788  n_pr++;
5789  if (!pr->pd_) {
5790  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*) pr;
5791  assert(glr->gl_->expr_);
5792  glr->fill_pd();
5793  if (pr->pd_) {
5794  n_trajec++;
5795  } else {
5796  n_trajec += glr->pd_and_vec_.size();
5797  }
5798  } else {
5799  n_trajec++;
5800  }
5801  } else if (pr->type() == GVectorRecordType) {
5802  GVectorRecord* gvr = (GVectorRecord*) pr;
5803  if (gvr->count()) {
5804  bsize = 0;
5805  n_pr++;
5806  for (int j = 0; j < gvr->count(); ++j) {
5807  if (gvr->pdata(j)) {
5808  n_trajec++;
5809  }
5810  }
5811  }
5812 #endif // HAVE_IV
5813  }
5814  }
5815  }
5816  if (n_pr == 0) {
5817  return;
5818  }
5819  vpr = new void*[n_pr];
5820  types = new int[n_trajec];
5821  indices = new int[n_trajec];
5822  if (bsize > 0) {
5823  varrays = new double*[n_trajec];
5824  } else {
5825  pvars = new double*[n_trajec];
5826  } // if both varrays and pvars are NULL then CoreNEURON will return values every time step
5827  // everything allocated, start over and fill
5828  n_pr = 0;
5829  n_trajec = 0;
5830  for (auto& pr: *fr) {
5831  int err = 0;
5832  if (pr->ith_ == tid) {
5833  if (1) { // buffered or per time step value return
5834  if (pr->type() == TvecRecordType) {
5835  IvocVect* v = ((TvecRecord*) pr)->t_;
5836  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5837  bsize,
5838  v,
5839  neuron::container::data_handle<double>{
5840  neuron::container::do_not_search, &nt._t},
5841  n_pr++,
5842  pr,
5843  vpr,
5844  n_trajec++,
5845  types,
5846  indices,
5847  pvars,
5848  varrays);
5849  if (err) {
5850  n_pr--;
5851  n_trajec--;
5852  }
5853  } else if (pr->type() == YvecRecordType) {
5854  IvocVect* v = ((YvecRecord*) pr)->y_;
5855  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5856  bsize,
5857  v,
5858  pr->pd_,
5859  n_pr++,
5860  pr,
5861  vpr,
5862  n_trajec++,
5863  types,
5864  indices,
5865  pvars,
5866  varrays);
5867  if (err) {
5868  n_pr--;
5869  n_trajec--;
5870  }
5871 #if HAVE_IV
5872  } else if (pr->type() == GLineRecordType) {
5873  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*) pr;
5874  if (pr->pd_) { // glr->gl_->name is an expression resolved to a double*
5875  if (bsize && !glr->v_) {
5876  glr->v_ = new IvocVect(bsize);
5877  }
5878  IvocVect* v = glr->v_;
5879  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5880  bsize,
5881  v,
5882  pr->pd_,
5883  n_pr++,
5884  pr,
5885  vpr,
5886  n_trajec++,
5887  types,
5888  indices,
5889  pvars,
5890  varrays);
5891  if (err) {
5892  n_pr--;
5893  n_trajec--;
5894  }
5895  } else { // glr->gl_->name expression involves several range variables
5896  int n = n_trajec;
5897  for (auto&& [pd, v]: glr->pd_and_vec_) {
5898  assert(pd);
5899  if (bsize && v == nullptr) {
5900  v = new IvocVect(bsize);
5901  }
5902  // TODO avoid the conversion?
5903  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5904  bsize,
5905  v,
5906  neuron::container::data_handle<double>{pd},
5907  n_pr,
5908  pr,
5909  vpr,
5910  n_trajec++,
5911  types,
5912  indices,
5913  pvars,
5914  varrays);
5915  if (err) {
5916  break;
5917  }
5918  }
5919  n_pr++;
5920  if (err) { // single error removes entire GLineRecord
5921  n_pr--;
5922  n_trajec = n;
5923  }
5924  }
5925  } else if (pr->type() == GVectorRecordType) {
5926  GVectorRecord* gvr = (GVectorRecord*) pr;
5927  if (gvr->count()) {
5928  int n = n_trajec;
5929  for (int j = 0; j < gvr->count(); ++j) {
5930  if (gvr->pdata(j)) {
5931  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5932  bsize,
5933  NULL,
5934  gvr->pdata(j),
5935  n_pr,
5936  pr,
5937  vpr,
5938  n_trajec++,
5939  types,
5940  indices,
5941  pvars,
5942  varrays);
5943  if (err) {
5944  break;
5945  }
5946  }
5947  }
5948  n_pr++;
5949  if (err) { // single error removes entire GVectorRecord
5950  n_pr--;
5951  n_trajec = n;
5952  }
5953  }
5954 #endif // HAVE_IV
5955  }
5956  }
5957  }
5958  }
5959  if (n_trajec == 0) { // if errors reduced to 0, clean up
5960  assert(n_pr == 0);
5961  delete[] std::exchange(types, nullptr);
5962  delete[] std::exchange(indices, nullptr);
5963  delete[] std::exchange(vpr, nullptr);
5964  delete[] std::exchange(varrays, nullptr);
5965  delete[] std::exchange(pvars, nullptr);
5966  }
5967 #if 0
5968  printf("nrnthread_get_trajectory_requests tid=%d bsize=%d n_pr=%d n_trajec=%d\n", tid, bsize, n_pr, n_trajec);
5969  int i_trajec = 0;
5970  double* pd;
5971  for (int i=0; i < n_pr; ++i) {
5972  PlayRecord* pr = (PlayRecord*)vpr[i];
5973  pd = pr->pd_;
5974  if (pd) {
5975  printf(" %d %d prtype=%d %p type=%d index=%d\n", i, i_trajec, pr->type(), pd, types[i_trajec], indices[i_trajec]);
5976  i_trajec++;
5977  }else{
5978  assert(pr->type() == GLineRecordType);
5979  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*)pr;
5980  GLineRecordEData& ed = glr->pd_and_vec_;
5981  i_trajec += ed.size();
5982  }
5983  }
5984 #endif
5985  }
5986 }

5988 void nrnthread_trajectory_values(int tid, int n_pr, void** vpr, double tt) { //, int n_trajec,
5989  // double* values) {
5990  if (tid < 0) {
5991  return;
5992  }
5993  if (tid < nrn_nthread) {
5994 #if HAVE_IV
5995  ObjectContext obc(NULL); // in case GLineRecord with expression.
5996 #endif // HAVE_IV
5997  nrn_threads[tid]._t = tt;
5998  if (tid == 0) {
5999  t = tt;
6000  }
6001  int flush = 0;
6002  for (int i = 0; i < n_pr; ++i) {
6003  PlayRecord* pr = (PlayRecord*) vpr[i];
6004  pr->continuous(tt);
6005 #if HAVE_IV
6006  if (pr->type() == GVectorRecordType) { // see the movie
6007  flush = 1;
6008  }
6009  }
6010  if (flush) {
6011  Oc oc;
6012  oc.run("screen_update()\n");
6013  }
6014 #else
6015  }
6016 #endif // HAVE_IV
6017  }
6018 }
6019 
6020 // CoreNEURON received pointers to the data of each Vector (resized so that
6021 // the data is long enough to hold the trajectory (tstop/dt). On calling
6022 // this, each Vector needs only be resized to the actual vecsz.
6023 // Note that we have not bothered to fill the variables on the hoc side with
6024 // the last values, though we did fill t.
6025 // In the case where glr->pd_ = NULL, the GraphLine is an expression that
6026 // cannot be interpreted as a pointer and the expression involves one or
6027 // more range variables that individually were resolved into pointers. In
6028 // this case in glr->plot, the relevant Vector elements are copied into those
6029 // pointers and the expression is then evaluated and plotted.
6030 void nrnthread_trajectory_return(int tid, int n_pr, int bsize, int vecsz, void** vpr, double tt) {
6031  if (tid < 0) {
6032  return;
6033  }
6034  if (tid < nrn_nthread) {
6035  nrn_threads[tid]._t = tt;
6036  if (tid == 0) {
6037  t = tt;
6038  }
6039  for (int i = 0; i < n_pr; ++i) {
6040  PlayRecord* pr = (PlayRecord*) vpr[i];
6041  IvocVect* v = NULL;
6042  if (pr->type() == TvecRecordType) {
6043  v = ((TvecRecord*) pr)->t_;
6044  // reserved bsize but only used vecsz. (need non-zeroing resize).
6045  v->resize(v->size() - (bsize - vecsz)); // do not zero
6046  } else if (pr->type() == YvecRecordType) {
6047  v = ((YvecRecord*) pr)->y_;
6048  v->resize(v->size() - (bsize - vecsz)); // do not zero
6049 #if HAVE_IV
6050  } else if (pr->type() == GLineRecordType) {
6051  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*) pr;
6052  glr->plot(vecsz, tt);
6053 #endif // HAVE_IV
6054  } else {
6055  assert(0);
6056  }
6057  }
6058  }
6059 }
6060 
6061 // factored this out from deliver_net_events so we can
6062 // stay in the cache
6063 void NetCvode::check_thresh(NrnThread* nt) { // for default method
6064  nrn::Instrumentor::phase p_check_threshold("check-threshold");
6065  hoc_Item* pth = p[nt->id].psl_thr_;
6066 
6067  if (pth) { /* only look at ones with a threshold */
6068  hoc_Item* q1;
6069  ITERATE(q1, pth) {
6070  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q1);
6071  // only the ones for this thread
6072  if (ps->nt_ == nt) {
6073  if (ps->thvar_) {
6074  ps->check(nt, nt->_t, 1e-10);
6075  }
6076  }
6077  }
6078  }
6079 
6080  for (HTList* wl: wl_list_[nt->id]) {
6081  for (HTList* item = wl->First(); item != wl->End(); item = item->Next()) {
6082  WatchCondition* wc = (WatchCondition*) item;
6083  wc->check(nt, nt->_t);
6084  }
6085  }
6086 }
6087 
6088 /** In nrncore_callbacks.cpp **/
6089 extern void nrn2core_transfer_WatchCondition(WatchCondition* wc,
6090  void (*cb)(int, int, int, int, int));
6091 extern "C" {
6092 void nrn2core_transfer_WATCH(void (*cb)(int, int, int, int, int));
6093 }
6094 void nrn2core_transfer_WATCH(void (*cb)(int, int, int, int, int)) {
6095  // should be revisited for possible simplification since wl_list now
6096  // segregated by threads.
6097  for (auto& htlists_of_thread: net_cvode_instance->wl_list_) {
6098  for (HTList* wl: htlists_of_thread) {
6099  for (HTList* item = wl->First(); item != wl->End(); item = item->Next()) {
6100  WatchCondition* wc = (WatchCondition*) item;
6101  nrn2core_transfer_WatchCondition(wc, cb);
6102  }
6103  }
6104  }
6105 }
6106 
6107 void NetCvode::deliver_net_events(NrnThread* nt) { // for default method
6108  TQItem* q;
6109  double tm, tsav;
6110 #if NRNMPI
6111  if (use_multisend_) {
6112  nrn_multisend_advance();
6113  }
6114 #endif
6115  int tid = nt->id;
6116  tsav = nt->_t;
6117  tm = nt->_t + 0.5 * nt->_dt;
6118 tryagain:
6119  // one of the events on the main queue may be a NetParEvent
6120  // which due to dt round off error can result in an event
6121  // placed on the bin queue to be delivered now, which
6122  // can put 0 delay events on to the main queue. So loop til
6123  // no events. The alternative would be to deliver an idt=0 event
6124  // immediately but that would very much change the sequence
6125  // with respect to what is being done here and it is unclear
6126  // how to fix the value of t there. This can be a do while loop
6127  // but I do not want to affect the case of not using a bin queue.
6128 
6129  if (nrn_use_bin_queue_) {
6130  // it was noticed on binq + compressed spike exchange +
6131  // threads that a transferred event may be languishing in
6132  // the interthread event buffer. Perhaps this is better done
6133  // as a multithread job at the end of nrn_spike_exchange
6134  // instead of every time step --- but here we are
6135  // already in a multithread job, so what is the overhead of
6136  // starting such a small one in nrn_spike_exchange.
6137 #if NRNMPI
6138  extern bool nrn_use_compress_;
6139  if (nrn_use_compress_ && nrn_nthread > 1) {
6140  p[tid].enqueue(this, nt);
6141  }
6142 #endif
6143  while ((q = p[tid].tqe_->dequeue_bin()) != 0) {
6144  DiscreteEvent* db = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
6145 #if PRINT_EVENT
6146  if (print_event_) {
6147  db->pr("binq deliver", nt_t, this);
6148  }
6149 #endif
6150  p[tid].tqe_->release(q);
6151  db->deliver(nt->_t, this, nt);
6152  }
6153  // assert(int(tm/nt->_dt)%1000 == p[tid].tqe_->nshift_);
6154  }
6155 
6156  deliver_events(tm, nt);
6157 
6158  if (nrn_use_bin_queue_) {
6159  if (p[tid].tqe_->top()) {
6160  goto tryagain;
6161  }
6162  p[tid].tqe_->shift_bin(tm);
6163  }
6164  nt->_t = tsav;
6165 }

6444 void NetCvode::vecrecord_add() {

6465 
6466 void NetCvode::playrec_setup() {
6467  long i, j;
6468  fixed_record_->clear();
6469  fixed_play_->clear();
6470  if (gcv_) {
6471  gcv_->delete_prl();
6472  } else {
6473  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6474  p[i].lcv_[j].delete_prl();
6475  }
6476  }
6477  std::vector<PlayRecord*> to_delete{};
6478  for (auto& pr: *prl_) {
6479  if (!pr->pd_) {
6480  // Presumably the recorded value was invalidated elsewhere, e.g. it
6481  // was a voltage of a deleted node, or a range variable of a deleted
6482  // mechanism instance
6483  to_delete.push_back(pr);
6484  continue;
6485  }
6486  bool b = false;
6487  if (single_) {
6488  pr->install(gcv_);
6489  b = true;
6490  } else {
6491  if (pr->ppobj_ && ob2pntproc(pr->ppobj_)->nvi_) {
6492  pr->install((Cvode*) ob2pntproc(pr->ppobj_)->nvi_);
6493  b = true;
6494  } else {
6495  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6496  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
6497  if (cv.is_owner(pr->pd_)) {
6498  pr->install(&cv);
6499  b = true;
6500  break;
6501  }
6502  }
6503  }
6504  }
6505  if (b == false) {
6506  hoc_execerror("We were unable to associate a PlayRecord item with a RANGE variable",
6507  nullptr);
6508  }
6509  // and need to know the thread owners
6510  if (pr->ppobj_) {
6511  i = PP2NT(ob2pntproc(pr->ppobj_))->id;
6512  } else {
6513  i = owned_by_thread(pr->pd_);
6514  }
6515  if (i < 0) {
6516  hoc_execerror("We were unable to associate a PlayRecord item with a thread", nullptr);
6517  }
6518  pr->ith_ = i;
6519  }
6520  for (auto* pr: to_delete) {
6521  // Destructor should de-register things
6522  delete pr;
6523  }
6524  playrec_change_cnt_ = structure_change_cnt_;
6525 }
6526 
6527 // is a pointer to range variable in this cell
6528 bool Cvode::is_owner(neuron::container::data_handle<double> const& handle) {
6529  int in, it;
6530  for (it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
6531  CvodeThreadData& z = CTD(it);
6532  for (in = 0; in < z.v_node_count_; ++in) {
6533  Node* nd = z.v_node_[in];
6534  if (handle == nd->v_handle()) {
6535  return true;
6536  }
6537  auto* pd = static_cast<double const*>(handle);
6538  Prop* p;
6539  for (p = nd->prop; p; p = p->next) {
6540  if (p->owns(handle)) {
6541  return true;
6542  }
6543  }
6544  if (nd->extnode) {
6545  if (pd >= nd->extnode->v && pd < (nd->extnode->v + nlayer)) {
6546  return true;
6547  }
6548  }
6549  // will need to check the linear mechanisms when there is a cvode
6550  // specific list of them and IDA is allowed for local step method.
6551  }
6552  if (nth_) {
6553  break;
6554  } // lvardt
6555  }
6556  return false;
6557 }
6558 
6559 int NetCvode::owned_by_thread(neuron::container::data_handle<double> const& handle) {
6560  if (nrn_nthread == 1) {
6561  return 0;
6562  }
6563  int in, it;
6564  for (it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
6565  NrnThread& nt = nrn_threads[it];
6566  int i1 = 0;
6567  int i3 = nt.end;
6568  for (in = i1; in < i3; ++in) {
6569  Node* nd = nt._v_node[in];
6570  if (handle == nd->v_handle()) {
6571  return it;
6572  }
6573  for (Prop* p = nd->prop; p; p = p->next) {
6574  if (p->owns(handle)) {
6575  return it;
6576  }
6577  }
6578  if (nd->extnode) {
6579  auto* pd = static_cast<double const*>(handle);
6580  if (pd >= nd->extnode->v && pd < (nd->extnode->v + nlayer)) {
6581  return it;
6582  }
6583  }
6584  // will need to check the line mechanisms when there is a cvode
6585  // specific list of them and IDA is allowed for local step method.
6586  }
6587  }
6588  return -1;
6589 }
6590 
6591 void NetCvode::consist_sec_pd(const char* msg,
6592  Section* sec,
6593  neuron::container::data_handle<double> const& handle) {
6594  int in;
6595  Node* nd;
6596  for (in = -1; in < sec->nnode; ++in) {
6597  if (in == -1) {
6598  nd = sec->parentnode; // in case &v(0)
6599  if (!nd) {
6600  continue;
6601  }
6602  } else {
6603  nd = sec->pnode[in];
6604  }
6605  if (nd->v_handle() == handle) {
6606  return;
6607  }
6608  Prop* p;
6609  auto* const pd = static_cast<double const*>(handle);
6610  for (p = nd->prop; p; p = p->next) {
6611  if (p->owns(handle)) {
6612  return;
6613  }
6614  }
6615  if (nd->extnode) {
6616  if (pd >= nd->extnode->v && pd < (nd->extnode->v + nlayer)) {
6617  return;
6618  }
6619  }
6620  // will need to check the linear mechanisms when there is a cvode
6621  // specific list of them and IDA is allowed for local step method.
6622  }
6623  hoc_execerror(msg,
6624  " pointer not associated with currently accessed section\n\
6625 Use section ... (&var(x)...) intead of ...(&section.var(x)...)\n");
6626 }
6627 
6628 double NetCvode::state_magnitudes() {
6629  if (hoc_is_double_arg(1)) {
6630  int on = (int) chkarg(1, 0, 2);
6631  int i, j;
6632  if (on == 2) {
6633  maxstate_analyse();
6634  } else {
6635  if (gcv_) {
6636  gcv_->activate_maxstate(on ? true : false);
6637  } else {
6638  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6639  p[i].lcv_[j].activate_maxstate(on ? true : false);
6640  }
6641  }
6642  }
6643  return 0.;
6644  } else if (hoc_is_str_arg(1)) {
6645  Symbol* sym = name2sym(gargstr(1));
6646  double dummy;
6647  double* pamax = &dummy;
6648  if (ifarg(2)) {
6649  pamax = hoc_pgetarg(2);
6650  }
6651  return maxstate_analyse(sym, pamax);
6652  } else {
6653  int i, j, n;
6654  Vect* v = vector_arg(1);
6655  if (!cvode_active_) {
6656  v->resize(0);
6657  return 0.;
6658  }
6659  double* vp;
6660  n = 0;
6661  if (gcv_) {
6662  n += gcv_->neq_;
6663  } else {
6664  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6665  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
6666  }
6667  }
6668  v->resize(n);
6669  vp = vector_vec(v);
6670  int getacor = 0;
6671  if (ifarg(2)) {
6672  getacor = (int) chkarg(2, 0, 1);
6673  }
6674  j = 0;
6675  if (gcv_) {
6676  if (gcv_->maxstate_) {
6677  if (getacor) {
6678  gcv_->maxacor(vp);
6679  } else {
6680  gcv_->maxstate(vp);
6681  }
6682  }
6683  } else {
6684  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6685  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
6686  if (cv.maxstate_) {
6687  if (getacor) {
6688  cv.maxacor(vp + j);
6689  } else {
6690  cv.maxstate(vp + j);
6691  }
6692  }
6693  j += cv.neq_;
6694  }
6695  }
6696  return 0.;
6697  }
6698 }
6699 void NetCvode::maxstate_analyze_1(int it, Cvode& cv, CvodeThreadData& z) {
6700  int j, n;
6701  Symbol* sym;
6702  double* ms;
6703  double* ma;
6704  n = z.nvsize_;
6705  ms = cv.n_vector_data(cv.maxstate_, it);
6706  ma = cv.n_vector_data(cv.maxacor_, it);
6707  auto const hdp = create_hdp(2);
6708  for (j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
6709  sym = hdp.retrieve_sym(static_cast<double*>(z.pv_[j]));
6710  auto msti = mst_->find((void*) sym);
6711  MaxStateItem* msi;
6712  if (msti == mst_->end()) {
6713  msi = new MaxStateItem();
6714  msi->sym_ = sym;
6715  msi->max_ = -1e9;
6716  msi->amax_ = -1e9;
6717  (*mst_)[(void*) sym] = msi;
6718  } else {
6719  msi = msti->second;
6720  }
6721  if (msi->max_ < ms[j]) {
6722  msi->max_ = ms[j];
6723  }
6724  if (msi->amax_ < ma[j]) {
6725  msi->amax_ = ma[j];
6726  }
6727  }
6728 }
6729 
6730 void NetCvode::maxstate_analyse() {
6731  int i, it, j;
6732  Symbol* sym;
6733  if (!mst_) {
6734  int n = 0;
6735  for (sym = hoc_built_in_symlist->first; sym; sym = sym->next) {
6736  ++n;
6737  }
6738  mst_ = new MaxStateTable(3 * n);
6739  }
6740  for (auto ti: *mst_) {
6741  MaxStateItem* msi = ti.second;
6742  msi->max_ = -1e9;
6743  msi->amax_ = -1e9;
6744  }
6745  if (empty_) {
6746  return;
6747  }
6748  statename(0, 2);
6749  if (gcv_) {
6750  for (it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
6751  maxstate_analyze_1(it, *gcv_, gcv_->ctd_[it]);
6752  }
6753  } else {
6754  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6755  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
6756  maxstate_analyze_1(i, cv, cv.ctd_[0]);
6757  }
6758  }
6759 }
6760 
6761 double NetCvode::maxstate_analyse(Symbol* sym, double* pamax) {
6762  if (mst_) {
6763  auto msti = mst_->find((void*) sym);
6764  if (msti != mst_->end()) {
6765  *pamax = msti->second->amax_;
6766  return msti->second->max_;
6767  }
6768  }
6769  *pamax = -1e9;
6770  return -1e9;
6771 }
6772 
6773 static double lvardt_tout_;
6774 
6775 static void lvardt_integrate(neuron::model_sorted_token const& token, NrnThread& ntr) {
6776  auto* const nt = &ntr;
6777  size_t err = NVI_SUCCESS;
6778  int id = nt->id;
6779  NetCvode* nc = net_cvode_instance;
6780  NetCvodeThreadData& p = nc->p[id];
6781  TQueue* tq = p.tq_;
6782  TQueue* tqe = p.tqe_;
6783  double tout = lvardt_tout_;
6784  nt->_stop_stepping = 0;
6785  while (tq->least_t() < tout || tqe->least_t() <= tout) {
6786  err = nc->local_microstep(token, ntr);
6787  if (nt->_stop_stepping) {
6788  nt->_stop_stepping = 0;
6789  return;
6790  }
6791  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6792  return;
6793  }
6794  }
6795  int n = p.nlcv_;
6796  Cvode* lcv = p.lcv_;
6797  if (n)
6798  for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
6799  nc->retreat(tout, lcv + i);
6800  lcv[i].record_continuous();
6801  }
6802  else {
6803  nt->_t = tout;
6804  }
6805 }
6806 
6807 int NetCvode::solve_when_threads(double tout) {
6808  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
6809  int tid;
6810  double til;
6811  nrn_use_busywait(1); // just a possibility
6812  auto const cache_token = nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted();
6813  if (empty_) {
6814  if (tout >= 0.) {
6815  while (nt_t < tout && !stoprun) {
6816  deliver_events_when_threads(tout);
6817  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6818  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6819  }
6820  }
6821  if (stoprun == 0) {
6822  nt_t = tout;
6823  }
6824  } else {
6825  if ((til = allthread_least_t(tid)) < 1e10) {
6826  deliver_events_when_threads(til);
6827  } else {
6828  nt_t += 1e6;
6829  }
6830  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6831  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6832  }
6833  }
6834  } else if (gcv_) {
6835  if (tout >= 0.) {
6836  while (gcv_->t_ < tout || allthread_least_t(tid) < tout) {
6837  err = global_microstep_when_threads();
6838  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6839  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6840  }
6841  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6842  return err;
6843  }
6844  }
6845  retreat(tout, gcv_);
6846  gcv_->record_continuous();
6847  } else {
6848  // advance or initialized
6849  double tc = gcv_->t_;
6850  initialized_ = false;
6851  while (gcv_->t_ <= tc && !initialized_) {
6852  err = global_microstep_when_threads();
6853  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6854  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6855  }
6856  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6857  return err;
6858  }
6859  }
6860  }
6861  } else { // lvardt
6862  if (tout >= 0.) {
6863  // Each thread could integrate independently to tout
6864  // as long as no thread got more than
6865  // a minimum delay interval ahead of any other.
6866  // For now just integrate by min delay intervals.
6867  lvardt_tout_ = tout;
6868  while (nt_t < tout) {
6869  nrn_multithread_job(cache_token, lvardt_integrate);
6870  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6871  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6872  }
6873  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6874  return err;
6875  }
6876  int tid;
6877  allthread_least_t(tid);
6878  }
6879  } else {
6880  // nthread>1 is more or less purposeless if we mean
6881  // that only the least cvode of all threads advances.
6882  // (which is required if minimum delay = 0)
6883  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
6884  hoc_execerror("Lvardt method from fadvance()",
6885  "presently limited to single thread.");
6886  }
6887  }
6888  }
6889  nrn_use_busywait(0);
6890  t = nt_t;
6891  dt = nt_dt;
6892  return err;
6893 }
6894 
6895 static void* deliver_for_thread(NrnThread* nt) {
6896  NetCvode* nc = net_cvode_instance;
6897  NetCvodeThreadData& d = nc->p[nt->id];
6898  TQItem* q = d.tqe_->least();
6899  DiscreteEvent* de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
6900  double tt = q->t_;
6901  d.tqe_->remove(q);
6902 #if PRINT_EVENT
6903  if (nc->print_event_) {
6904  de->pr("deliver", tt, nc);
6905  }
6906 #endif
6907  de->deliver(tt, nc, nt);
6908  return 0;
6909 }
6910 
6911 void NetCvode::deliver_events_when_threads(double til) {
6912  // printf("deliver_events til %20.15g\n", til);
6913  int tid;
6914  while (allthread_least_t(tid) <= til) {
6915  STATISTICS(deliver_cnt_);
6916  nrn_onethread_job(tid, deliver_for_thread);
6917  if (stoprun || nrn_allthread_handle) {
6918  return;
6919  }
6920  }
6921 }
6922 
6923 int NetCvode::global_microstep_when_threads() {
6924  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
6925  int tid;
6926  double tt = allthread_least_t(tid);
6927  double tdiff = tt - gcv_->t_;
6928  if (tdiff <= 0) {
6929  // since events do not internally retreat with the
6930  // global step, we should already be at the event time
6931  // if this is too strict, we could use eps(list_->t_).
6932  // if (tdiff != 0.0) { printf("tdiff=%g\n", tdiff); }
6933  assert(tdiff == 0.0 || (gcv_->tstop_begin_ <= tt && tt <= gcv_->tstop_end_));
6934  deliver_events_when_threads(tt);
6935  } else {
6936  err = gcv_->handle_step(nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted(), this, tt);
6937  }
6938  if ((tt = allthread_least_t(tid)) < gcv_->t_) {
6939  gcv_->interpolate(tt);
6940  }
6941  return err;
6942 }

6945  net_cvode_instance->p[nt->id].enqueue(net_cvode_instance, nt);
6946  return 0;
6947 }

6954 
6955 double NetCvode::allthread_least_t(int& tid) {
6956  // reduce (take minimum) of p[i].tqe_->least_t()
6957  double tt, min = 1e50;
6958  // setting enqueueing_ in interthread_send was a race. Logically it is not
6959  // needed. It is not clear if higher performance would result in having
6960  // a MUTEX for the NetCvode instance but that is the current implementation
6961  // instead of commenting out the enqueuing related lines.
6962  if (enqueueing_) {
6963  nrn_multithread_job(nrn_interthread_enqueue);
6964  enqueueing_ = 0;
6965  }
6966  for (int id = 0; id < pcnt_; ++id) {
6967  tt = p[id].tqe_->least_t();
6968  if (tt < min) {
6969  tid = id;
6970  min = tt;
6971  }
6972  }
6973  return min;
6974 }
